<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-25T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-25T06:00:00-05:00" n="770" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">119.2/3017: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                        (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-25T12:00:00+01:00">September 25, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September
                                        25—7:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>466. My 459, September 20, 5 p.m.<note n="95" xml:id="d770fn95">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office states Admiralty is
                                    prepared to relay United States Government messages on strictly
                                    Government business only between the United States Legation at
                                    Addis Ababa and Aden wireless station at Aden from 8:30 to 9:30
                                    a.m. Greenwich mean time. “Frequency will be 10345 kilocycles
                                    (slightly under 30 meters wave length).” This service to cost
                                    one-half normal rate.</p>
                                <p>Should Department accept this proposal Foreign Office suggests
                                    further consultation with Embassy as to determining moment when
                                    service should commence.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>